Well, that was an informative blast
from the somewhat recent past.

00:02:15.710 --> 00:02:17.660
Man, I can't believe that
just three months ago,

00:02:17.660 --> 00:02:20.090
I was sitting at a meeting with
the Bay Area Shoppers Group.

00:02:20.090 --> 00:02:22.650
&gt;&gt; You've come a long way, and
you've come a long way too.

00:02:22.650 --> 00:02:24.930
You now know how to read
data into Firebase.

00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:26.580
&gt;&gt; You also know how
to take that data and

00:02:26.580 --> 00:02:29.020
display it in real
time in a Firebase app.

00:02:29.020 --> 00:02:30.320
&gt;&gt; Let's not forget users.

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:32.680
You also know how to create
authentication methods for

00:02:32.680 --> 00:02:35.250
email and
another provider such as Google.

00:02:35.250 --> 00:02:38.440
&gt;&gt; And you've learned how to create
firebase data schemas to avoid things

00:02:38.440 --> 00:02:41.370
like nesting data while also
denormalizing your data.

00:02:41.370 --> 00:02:43.920
This really helps you grow and
scale your apps.

00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:45.910
&gt;&gt; You've also learned how to filter and
sort your data.

00:02:45.910 --> 00:02:48.975
&gt;&gt; Finally, we learned how to use
Firebase's security rules language to

00:02:48.975 --> 00:02:50.630
make our apps status secure.

00:02:50.630 --> 00:02:52.380
&gt;&gt; That's a lot.
&gt;&gt; That is a lot.

00:02:53.690 --> 00:02:54.540
You know what?

00:02:54.540 --> 00:02:56.390
I feel like you deserve
this API as much as I do.

00:02:56.390 --> 00:03:02.310
&gt;&gt; Yeah but more than a cell phone
duct taped to a cheap trophy,

00:03:02.310 --> 00:03:05.130
we hope you feel empowered to
create your own apps in Firebase.

00:03:05.130 --> 00:03:06.160
&gt;&gt; Actually that reminds me,

00:03:06.160 --> 00:03:09.000
I have another venture that I
wanted to talk to you about.

